text: Update on "Where in the world is my laptop". @Klarna was able to get me a tracking number yesterday, after being told on Friday by @Microsoft that my order hadn't shipped. Best part is @FedEx says that the package was delivered on the 3rd. But I still have yet to get anything.

@MicrosoftHelps @Microsoft it’s been two weeks since my package was delivered according to @FedEx but I still see my order as “Awaiting Fulfillment”. Been on hold for over half an hour trying to talk to someone. Missing a package worth over $2,000 is kind of a big deal.

@Klarna doesn’t require a signature on a $2,000+ package. @FedEx delivers to the wrong apartment. @Microsoft sends shipping confirmation email TWO WEEKS after the package is delivered. But I STILL can’t get a refund. #poorservice #NeverAgain

It's been over a week since I opened a lost package case with @FedEx & a support case with @Microsoft/@MicrosoftHelps about a missing laptop worth over $2,400. Still waiting on a resolution. Not having a computer is going to make it difficult to start MBA classes on Monday. #HELP

Almost two months later and there is still no word from @Microsoft/@MicrosoftHelps or @FedEx/@FedExHelp about a missing package worth almost $2,500. Simply that they are still looking into it and will get back to me as soon as they know more. TWO MONTHS. #badcustomerservice

@Galen_Henseler @Galen_Henseler Hello, this is Joe. I do apologize on behalf of Fedex for this package and delivery issue. . Please DM @FedExHelp recipient name, delivery address, tracking & phone numbers. I would be happy to research this.
~joe
